text: Hazem Abdel Aziz El Beblawi (born 17 October 1936) is an Egyptian politician. He became the interim Prime Minister of Egypt in July 2013 after the 2013 Egypt protest which caused Mohamed Morsi out of office. On 25 February 2014, he announced his resignation. ==References== ==Other websites== * Egyptian State Information Service CV Category:1936 births Category:Living people Category:Egyptian Muslims Category:Politicians from Cairo Category:Prime Ministers of Egypt Category:21st-century rulers in Africa
